==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marching
<hw>March"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos>, fr.
<er>March</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Marching money</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>the
additional pay of officer or soldier when his regiment is marching.</cd>
-- <col><b>In marching order</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>equipped
for a march.</cd> -- <col><b>Marching regiment</b></col>.
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A regiment in active service</cd>.
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>In England, a regiment liable to be ordered into other
quarters, at home or abroad; a regiment of the line.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marchioness</ent>⟦br⟧
